    <h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 13 November 2025</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        BurgerJoint (Pty) Ltd (“we”, “our”, “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information.
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose and safeguard your data when you visit
        <a href="https://burgerjoint.co.za">https://burgerjoint.co.za</a> or any related services (the “Site”).
        We comply with the Protection of Personal Information Act 4 of 2013 (POPIA) and, where applicable,
        the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>2. What information do we collect?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account data:</strong> name, email, phone number, delivery address (only if you create an account or place an order).</li>
        <li><strong>Order data:</strong> items purchased, payment method, transaction reference (we do NOT store card numbers).</li>
        <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited, time-zone, device identifiers.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> see section 7 below.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing preferences:</strong> opt-in/opt-out status for newsletters or SMS.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How do we collect it?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Directly: when you register, place an order, complete a contact form or subscribe to a newsletter.</li>
        <li>Automatically: through cookies, log files, analytics and tracking technologies.</li>
        <li>Third parties: payment gateway (PayFast, Stripe) provides transaction status; delivery partners provide tracking updates.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Lawful basis under POPIA & GDPR</h2>
    <table class="table table-sm">
        <thead><tr><th>Activity</th><th>POPIA basis</th><th>GDPR article</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Creating an account</td><td>Contract</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Processing payment</td><td>Legal obligation + Contract</td><td>Art. 6(1)(b)(c)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Marketing emails (opt-in)</td><td>Consent</td><td>Art. 6(1)(a)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Analytics cookies</td><td>Legitimate interest</td><td>Art. 6(1)(f)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>5. Why do we use your data?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Fulfil orders, deliveries and returns.</li>
        <li>Process payments and prevent fraud.</li>
        <li>Send order updates and support messages.</li>
        <li>Improve products, website performance and customer experience.</li>
        <li>Comply with tax, accounting and other legal obligations.</li>
        <li>Send promotional offers (only with your consent, which you may withdraw at any time).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Sharing your data</h2>
    <p>We never sell your data. We only share it with:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Payment processors</strong> (PCI-DSS compliant).</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery couriers</strong> (to fulfil your order).</li>
        <li><strong>IT service providers</strong> (hosting, email, analytics).</li>
        <li><strong>Regulators or law-enforcement</strong> when legally required.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Cookies & tracking</h2>
    <h3>7.1 Essential cookies</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Session ID – keeps you logged in.</li>
        <li>Anti-forgery token – security.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7.2 Analytics cookies</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Google Analytics 4 – aggregated traffic analysis (IP anonymised).</li>
        <li>Hotjar – heat-maps (no personal data captured).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7.3 Marketing cookies</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Facebook Pixel – conversion tracking (only if you consent).</li>
    </ul>

    <p>You can manage cookies via the bottom-left “Cookie Settings” link or your browser settings. Rejecting non-essential cookies will not break core functionality.</p>

    <h2>8. International transfers</h2>
    <p>We host data in South Africa (Azure SA North).  
       Some analytics providers (Google, Facebook) may process data in the USA.  
       We rely on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) and/or your explicit consent for these transfers.</p>

    <h2>9. Data retention</h2>
    <table class="table table-sm">
        <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>Retention period</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Order invoices</td><td>5 years</td><td>SARS tax law</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Account details</td><td>Until account deleted</td><td>Contract</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Marketing consent</td><td>Until withdrawn + 30 days</td><td>Audit</td></tr>
